clinical_study.brief_title: A Study of Treprostinil and a New Formulation of LY900014 in Healthy Japanese Participants
clinical_study.official_title: A Study to Evaluate the Safety and Tolerability of Subcutaneous Treprostinil and Pharmacokinetics of a Novel LY900014 Formulation in Healthy Japanese Subjects

brief_summary.textblock:
The aims of this study are to evaluate:
- The safety and tolerability of a single dose of treprostinil given subcutaneously (as an injection just under the skin)
- The pharmacokinetic profile (how the body absorbs, breaks down, and gets rid of) of a single subcutaneous dose of a new LY900014 formulation in healthy Japanese participants.
The study has two parts. Participants may only enroll in one part.

primary_outcome.measure: Number of Participants with One or More Serious Adverse Event(s) (SAEs) Considered by the Investigator to be Related to Study Drug Administration
primary_outcome.time_frame: Part A: Baseline through Study Completion (up to 14 days after last dose)

primary_outcome.measure: Pharmacokinetics: Maximum Concentration (Cmax) of Insulin Lispro
primary_outcome.time_frame: Predose through 7 hours postdose in each period

primary_outcome.measure: Pharmacokinetics: Area Under the Concentration-Time Curve from Time Zero to 30 Minutes (AUC[0-30min]) of Insulin Lispro
primary_outcome.time_frame: Predose through 7 hours postdose in each period

secondary_outcome.measure: Pharmacokinetics: Time to Maximum Concentration (Tmax) of Treprostinil
secondary_outcome.time_frame: Predose through 2 hours postdose in each period
Predose through 2 hours postdose in each period

arm_group.description: Treprostinil administered as a single subcutaneous (SC) bolus injection.
Placebo administered as a single SC bolus injection.
LY900014 (test) administered as a single SC bolus injection.
Insulin lispro (reference) administered as a single SC bolus injection.

criteria.textblock:
Inclusion Criteria:
- Overtly healthy Japanese
- Body mass index (BMI) 18.5 - 25 kilograms per square meter (kg/m²)
- Fasting plasma glucose ≥71 milligrams per deciliter (mg/dL) (3.9 millimoles per liter [mmol/L]) and <108 mg/dL (6.0 mmol/L) (Part B only)
- Have normal blood pressure, pulse rate, electrocardiogram (ECG), blood and urine laboratory test results that are acceptable for the study
Exclusion Criteria:
- Are currently enrolled in a clinical trial involving an investigational product or any other type of medical research judged not to be scientifically or medically compatible with this study
- Have participated in a clinical trial involving an investigational product within the 30 days before study entry.
- Have previously completed or withdrawn from this study or any other study investigating treprostinil or LY900014, and have previously received the investigational product
- Have or used to have health problems or laboratory test results or ECG readings that, in the opinion of the doctor, could make it unsafe to participate, or could interfere with understanding the results of the study
